// The Variety Pack mod: the DOGFOOD for mods shipping their own binary
// resources (task 20260716-123544). Unlike every other bundle, whose asset
// refs point at BASE files under `assets/`, this bundle ships its own skybox
// and asteroid texture and references them with mod-relative `self://` paths
// that resolve against THIS folder (`assets/mods/variety/`) - or, once the mod
// is published and downloaded, against `mods://variety/`.
//
// `resources` lists the binary files the bundle ships (bundle-dir-relative, the
// same base as `content` and `meta.icon`). A `self://` content ref may only
// name a listed resource; the portal generator, the static content lint and the
// runtime content gate all reject an undeclared one. The skybox's `.meta`
// sidecar (nebula.png.meta, the RowCount cube reinterpret) rides along
// automatically and is NOT listed here.
//
// The textures here are PLACEHOLDERS (debug-colored). Real art replaces them
// under task 20260716-205214, keeping these paths.
(
    content: ["variety.content.ron"],
    resources: [
        "textures/nebula.png",
        "textures/rock.png",
    ],
    meta: (
        name: "Variety Pack",
        description: "Ships its own skybox and asteroid texture; a scenario that renders from mod-owned art, not base assets.",
        author: "Nova Protocol",
        version: "0.1.0",
        dependencies: ["base"],
    ),
)
